        <div id="welcomenote" style="width:45%;float:left;margin-left:0;height:100%;">
            <p style="font-size:24px;font-weight:bold;margin-bottom:2px;padding:0px 10px 2px 30px">Welcome to 4DGenome,
                a general repository for chromatin interaction data.
            </p>
            <p style="margin-top:8px;padding:0px 17px 2px 32px; font-size:19px;font-family:Times New Roman, Georgia,Serif;">
                Records in 4DGenome are compiled through comprehensive literature curation of experimentally-derived and
                computationally-predicted interactions. The current release contains 4,433,071 experimentally-derived
                and 3,605,176 computationally-predicted
                interactions in 5 organisms. Experimental data cover both high throughput datasets and individiual
                focused studies.
                <br><br>
                All interaction data are freely available in a standardized file format. Records can be queried by
                genomic regions, gene names, organism, and detection technology.
                <br><br>
            </p>
